# Cursor Rules for Andrii Lytvynenko's Portfolio Website

## Project Overview
This is a personal portfolio website for Andrii Lytvynenko, a Senior DevOps & Cloud Engineer. The site is a Progressive Web App (PWA) built with vanilla JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap, and jQuery.

**Live URL:** https://alytvynenko.net

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router) with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Framer Motion for animations
- Static export for GitHub Pages deployment
- Python for image optimization utilities

## Code Style and Formatting

### General
- **Indentation:** Use TABS for HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files (not spaces)
- **Line endings:** LF (Unix-style)
- **Encoding:** UTF-8
- **File naming:** Use kebab-case for files (e.g., `u1-certificates.js`)
- **Comments:** Write clear, concise comments for complex logic

### HTML
- Use tabs for indentation (consistent with existing codebase)
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- Always include proper meta tags (SEO, Open Graph, Twitter Cards)
- Include Content Security Policy headers
- Use `loading="lazy"` for images below the fold
- Use `loading="eager"` for above-the-fold images
- Always specify `width` and `height` attributes on images
- Use WebP format for images (converted from PNG)
- Include `alt` attributes with descriptive text for all images
- Use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` for external links with `target="_blank"`
- Include proper `aria-label` attributes for accessibility
- Structure: DOCTYPE → html → head → body → scripts at bottom

### CSS
- Use CSS Custom Properties (variables) defined in `:root`
- Prefix custom properties with context: `--color-`, `--spacing-`, `--font-`, etc.
- Use modern CSS features: Grid, Flexbox, custom properties
- Include responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: 980px, 768px, 600px, 400px, 320px
- Include `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` for accessibility
- Use `var(--variable-name)` for all color, spacing, and typography values
- Write CSS in logical order: positioning → box model → typography → visual → animations
- Use BEM-like naming for custom classes when applicable
- Include proper focus indicators for accessibility (`:focus-visible`)
- Font loading: Use `font-display: swap` for custom fonts

### JavaScript
- Use modern ES6+ syntax (const, let, arrow functions, template literals)
- Wrap code in try-catch blocks for error handling
- Use `document.createElement()` for DOM manipulation (not innerHTML for dynamic content)
- Use DocumentFragment for batch DOM insertions (performance)
- Check for element existence before manipulating (`if (!element) { throw error }`)
- Provide fallback messages when JavaScript fails to load
- Use descriptive variable names (e.g., `certificates_section`, `cert_data`)
- Comment complex logic and data structures
- Validate data before rendering
- Use strict equality (`===`, `!==`) over loose equality
- Add proper error logging with `console.error()`

## Performance Best Practices

### Images
- Use WebP format for all images (except favicon)
- Convert images using `tools/png_to_webp.py` utility
- Specify explicit width and height on all images
- Use `loading="lazy"` for below-fold images
- Optimize image quality (balance between size and visual quality)

### Loading
- Preload critical resources with `<link rel="preconnect">`
- Use DNS prefetch for third-party domains
- Load scripts at the bottom of the body (before closing `</body>`)
- Use async/defer for third-party scripts (Google Analytics)
- Implement Service Worker for offline caching

### Caching
- Service Worker caches critical assets
- Update `CACHE_NAME` version when deploying changes
- Cache strategy: Cache-first with network fallback
- Clean up old caches on activation

## Accessibility Requirements (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Include skip navigation link (`<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">`)
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Include screen reader only text with `.sr-only` class
- Ensure proper focus indicators (3px outline with offset)
- Support keyboard navigation
- Include `lang` attribute on `<html>` element
- Use sufficient color contrast ratios
- Support reduced motion preferences
- Provide text alternatives for all images
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)

## SEO Optimization
- Include canonical URL
- Meta description (150-160 characters)
- Open Graph tags for social sharing
- Twitter Card tags
- JSON-LD structured data (Schema.org Person type)
- Proper heading hierarchy
- Descriptive page titles
- Include `robots.txt` and `sitemap.xml`
- Use descriptive alt text for images

## Security Practices
- Implement Content Security Policy (CSP) headers
  - Include `https://www.googletagmanager.com` and `https://www.google-analytics.com` for Google Analytics
- Use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` on external links
- Sanitize any user input (if applicable)
- Use HTTPS for all external resources
- Keep dependencies updated

## Progressive Web App (PWA)
- Include `manifest.json` with app metadata
- Register Service Worker in main HTML
- Define offline caching strategy
- Use appropriate theme colors
- Include app icons in various sizes
- Set proper display mode (`standalone`)

## File Structure and Organization
```
/
├── src/
│   ├── app/               # Next.js App Router (layout, page, globals.css)
│   ├── components/       # React components (layout, bento, hero, ui)
│   └── data/             # TypeScript data (certificates, education, experiences, profile)
├── public/               # Static assets (images, pdf, CNAME, .nojekyll)
├── tools/
│   └── png_to_webp.py    # Image optimization
├── design/               # Design documentation
├── robots.txt
├── sitemap.xml
└── CNAME                 # Custom domain
```

## JavaScript Module Naming Convention
- `u0-` prefix: Utility/preloader scripts
- `u1-`, `u2-`, `u3-`: Content rendering modules (numbered by section order)
- Use descriptive names after prefix (e.g., `u1-certificates.js`)

## Content Structure Pattern
Each content section (certificates, education, experiences) follows this pattern:
1. Error handling wrapper (try-catch)
2. DOM element validation
3. Data object definition
4. DocumentFragment for performance
5. Loop through data and create elements
6. Append fragment to DOM
7. Error fallback with user-friendly message

## Data Structure Pattern
Content data objects follow this structure:
```javascript
const data = {
  "items": [
    {
      "title": "Title",
      "field": "value",
      // ... other fields
    }
  ]
}
```

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Test on multiple device sizes
- Use relative units (rem, em, %, vw/vh) where appropriate
- Flexible images (`max-width: 100%`)
- Responsive typography with media queries
- Touch-friendly targets (minimum 44x44px)

## Color Palette (Brand Colors)
- Primary: `#3366CC` (`var(--color-primary)`)
- Primary Dark: `#204090` (`var(--color-primary-dark)`)
- Accent: `#66CCFF` (`var(--color-accent)`)
- White: `#FFFFFF` (`var(--color-white)`)
- Dark: `#202020` (`var(--color-dark)`)
- Always use CSS variables, never hardcode colors

## Typography
- Primary font: Proxima Nova Regular
- Bold font: Proxima Nova Bold
- Fallback: System fonts (-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Roboto)
- Base font size: 16px (responsive down to 14px on small screens)

